<exercise number="41"><statement><p>Is <m>(x-3)^2</m> equivalent to <m>x^2-3^2 ~</m>?  Explain why or why not, and give a numerical example to justify your answer.</p></statement>
<answer><p>No. Let <m>x=1</m>, then <m>(x-1)^2=(-2)^2=4</m>, but <m>x^2-3^2=1-9=-8</m></p></answer></exercise>

